accessibility.text: Source: Pager, D., Western, B., & Sugie, N. (2009, May). Sequencing Disadvantage: Barriers to Employment Facing Young Black and White Men with Criminal Records. The ANNALS of the American Academy of Political and Social Science, 623, 195-213. 10.1177/0002716208330793
An arrest or conviction record reduces a job seekers chance of getting a callback or job offer by nearly 50 percent.
